Microsculpture . Sclerotised parts of the body ( e.g. cephalic capsule, mouthparts, thoracic and abdominal tergites, legs, pygidium) smooth or only slightly corrugated. Epipharynx and hypopharynx medially with pointed or multipointed microsculpture, arranged in many parallel, transverse rows; anterior margin of frontal emargination and sides of hypopharynx with tufts of thin elongate sculpticells (
Fig. 9
). Membranous areas of the body completely covered by a carpet of thorn-like spiniform warts by thin, elongate, filiform apices, shortening towards sclerotised areas (
Figs. 10
, 15–17 ). Surface of the terminal disk with spinulate microsculpture (
Figs. 21, 23
), composed of conical, pointed sculpticells (average length 4–7 mm , see
Fig. 23
). Pygidium smooth.

