Figs. 3, 5
); long seta FR 2 * posterior to FR 1 *; FR 3 * elongate, posteromedial; FR 4 * and FR 5 * transversally lined (FR 4 * slightly anterior to FR 5 *) at base of median emargination; small seta FR 6 * near and slightly posterior to FR 7 *; long seta FR 7 * on anterior margin, forwardly directed; setae FR 8 *, FR 10 * FR 11 * internal to FR 7 *, lined along anterior margin, bent mediad; pores FR a* FR c* FR d* FR e* present on frontal sclerite, FR b* FR f* absent. Each half of parietal plate (
Figs. 4, 6
